Stevinson first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Stevinson had a population of 275. The population density was {{convert|243.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Stevinson was 171 (62.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (0.4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.4%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 79 (28.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 23 (8.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 133 persons (48.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Stevinson CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0674144 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 81 households, out of which 39 (48.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 46 (56.8%) were married-couple households, 6 (7.4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 13 (16.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 16 (19.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 5 households (6.2%) were one person, and 1 (1.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.4.<ref name=DP1/> There were 70 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (86.4% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Stevinson CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0674144 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 79 people (28.7%) under the age of 18, 21 people (7.6%) aged 18 to 24, 64 people (23.3%) aged 25 to 44, 71 people (25.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 40 people (14.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 37.3{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 111.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 85 housing units at an average density of {{convert|75.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 81 (95.3%) were occupied. Of these, 47 (58.0%) were owner-occupied, and 34 (42.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

